    <widget class="QWidget" name="tab_DCS">
     <attribute name="title">
      <string>DCS</string>
     </attribute>
     <widget class="QLabel" name="labelDateTime_14">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>10</x>
        <y>10</y>
        <width>375</width>
        <height>23</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <property name="styleSheet">
       <string notr="true">background-color: rgb(153, 193, 241);</string>
      </property>
      <property name="text">
       <string>DCS: Direct Current Stimulation</string>
      </property>
      <property name="alignment">
       <set>Qt::AlignCenter</set>
      </property>
     </widget>
     <widget class="QLabel" name="labelLogoDCS">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>10</x>
        <y>40</y>
        <width>110</width>
        <height>110</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <property name="styleSheet">
       <string notr="true">background-color: rgb(153, 193, 241);</string>
      </property>
      <property name="text">
       <string/>
      </property>
     </widget>
     <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit_5">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>133</x>
        <y>40</y>
        <width>251</width>
        <height>171</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <property name="markdown">
       <string>ION-Sim: DCS module. Direct current stimulation. Usually performed using a
monopolar or bipolar stimulation electrode (two tips spaced 5-6 mm apart or a
coaxial spherical type with a diameter of about 1.7 mm). These geometric
configurations allow stimulation pulses to flow from the cathode (in the case
of the coaxial tip: connected to the central tip) and the anode (connected to
the peripheral tip) to the excitable nerve tissue below. This configuration
allows for extremely focal and precise stimulation of the structures to be
tested: it can be a peripheral or cranial nerve trunk (e.g., facial nerve in
the posterior cranial fossa) or the posterior columns of the spinal cord or the
entry zone of the posterior horns. Each of these settings requires a different
type of response recording, fundamentally reducible to two categories: motor
responses recordable from target muscles and sensory responses recordable at
the cortical level or from the scalp in the region/area corresponding to S1, 2,
3.

</string>
      </property>
     </widget>
    </widget>
    <widget class="QWidget" name="tab_EEG">
     <attribute name="title">
      <string>EEG</string>
     </attribute>
     <widget class="QLabel" name="labelDateTime_7">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>10</x>
        <y>10</y>
        <width>375</width>
        <height>23</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <property name="styleSheet">
       <string notr="true">background-color: rgb(153, 193, 241);</string>
      </property>
      <property name="text">
       <string>EEG: EEG Signal Simulator</string>
      </property>
      <property name="alignment">
       <set>Qt::AlignCenter</set>
      </property>
     </widget>
     <widget class="QLabel" name="labelLogoEeg">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>10</x>
        <y>40</y>
        <width>110</width>
        <height>110</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <property name="styleSheet">
       <string notr="true">background-color: rgb(153, 193, 241);</string>
      </property>
      <property name="text">
       <string/>
      </property>
     </widget>
     <widget class="QTextEdit" name="textEdit_6">
      <property name="geometry">
       <rect>
        <x>132</x>
        <y>40</y>
        <width>251</width>
        <height>171</height>
       </rect>
      </property>
      <property name="markdown">
       <string>ION-Sim: EEG module. The signal recorded from a real recording session with a
32-channel device at a 512 Hz sampling rate is used in the simulation. It is
possible to verify the signal characteristics, filtering, the presence of
specific artifacts, and the effects due to different referencing methods of the
channels used. Issues related to the spectral content of the signals and the
evaluation of auxiliary signals such as EOG and ECG are also illustrated.

</string>
      </property>
     </widget>
    </widget>
